<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <h3 style="text-align: center;">Joining Societies and Organization </h3>
    <br>
  </div>
  <div class="row justify-content-center"">
    <div class=" col-md-6 col-xs-12 col-sm-12">

    <details>
      <summary><strong>College of Radiology</strong></summary>
      <br>
      <p>
        <b>Why join COR?</b><br>
        <b>COR</b> is an organization led by radiologist for radiologist. By joining <b>COR</b>, you will be part of the
        present
        and future of radiology in Malaysia whilst safeguarding and improving the practice of patient care,
        and advancing the science of radiology/biomedical imaging/clinical oncology/nuclear medicine
        through adoption of newer proven technologies and treatment modalities.
        <br><br>
        <b>COR</b> will connect you with clinical radiologists, clinical oncologists, medical physicists and allied
        professionals who aim to ensure that radiology is an essential part of the health care medical system.
        <br><br>
        Joining <b>COR</b> means you will be supporting activities in 3 main areas:
        <br>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <b>Quality and Safety: COR</b> regularly works with government and healthcare
            professionals to improve the quality of patient care with better outcomes, cost-effectiveness
            and safety.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Advocacy: COR</b> is fast becoming the voice of radiology in Malaysia by
            positively influencing the socio-economics of the practice of radiology/biomedical
            imaging/clinical oncology/nuclear medicine.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Education: COR</b> creates opportunities for continuing medical education
            and research for radiology/biomedical imaging/clinical oncology/nuclear medicine and allied
            health professions.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <br>
        <b>What benefits does COR membership provide? </b>
        <br>
        <ul>
          <li>A local and common voice for radiologist in Malaysia</li>
          <li>Discounted fees at COR organized seminars, both international and local for instance; SIG
            Seminars and MCOR </li>
          <li>Access to radiology resources such as the Guidelines for Clinical Practices in Radiology</li>
          <li>Opportunities to form and collaborate in a task force to tackle current issues faced by fellow
            peers</li>
          <li>Access to fellow allied professionals via online chat groups for technical support and guidance</li>
          <li>Ability to receive firsthand information on new and common practices in the radiology field</li>
          <li>Access and information to workshops, seminars and congresses related to radiology</li>
          <li>Forging closer relationships with other colleges to form partnerships in post graduate training
            and research activities</li>
          <li>Participating in educational community projects</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <b>Types of Membership</b>
        <br>
        <i>Ordinary Membership</i>
        <br>
        <ul>
          <li>Fully registered radiologists and oncologists who; are certified to be specialists by the
            appropriate authorities, have a recognized postgraduate or higher qualification, are of good
            character and conduct and have been testified by three referees, two of whom must be
            members of the Academy of Medicine of Malaysia.</li>
          <li>Membership fees: <b>RM650.00</b> (RM500 for entrance fee and RM150 for first year annual subscription).
            An annual fee of <b>RM150</b> must be paid by every third quarter of each year.</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <i>Associate Membership</i>
        <br>
        <ul>
          <li>Allied practitioners who do not fulfill the Ordinary membership criteria of the Academy of
            Medicine of Malaysia. e.g. persons in allied professions involved in medical research who are
            able to further the interest of the Academy of Medicine of Malaysia.</li>
          <li>Membership fees: <b>RM650.00</b> (RM500 for entrance fee and RM150 for first year annual subscription).
            An annual fee of <b>RM150</b> must be paid by every third quarter of each year.</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <i>Candidate Membership</i>
        <br>
        <ul>
          <li>Fully registered medical who; are undergoing a recognised training programme, have passed
            the first part of a recognised professional graduate postgraduate diploma examination.
            Candidate members may retain their membership for a period not exceeding six years.</li>
          <li>Membership fees: <b>RM100.00</b> for first year subscription and an annual fee of <b>RM100</b> must be
            paid by every third quarter of each year.</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <i>Lifetime Membership</i>
        <br>
        <p>Requirements are as per Ordinary Membership but the fees vary. See below for description.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>For <b>non-COR members below 50 years of age;</b> RM3000 (RM2500 for entrance fee and RM500
            for admin fee)</li>
          <li>For <b>COR members below 50 years of ages;</b> RM2500 (there will be no charge for admin fees)</li>
          <li>For <b>non-COR members above 50 years of age;</b> RM1500 (RM1500 for entrance fees and
            RM500 for admin fees)</li>
          <li>For <b>COR Members above 50 years of age;</b> RM1000 (there will be no charge for admin fees)</li>
        </ul>
        <br>

        <b>How to Become a COR Member?</b>
        <br><br>
        <p>As COR is under the umbrella body of the Academy of Medicine of Malaysia; to join COR one joins the
          Academy of Medicine, but under the College of Radiology. </p>
        <p>All applications must be filled in and signed by the applicant and must be accompanied by;</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Basic medical degree(s) - certified true copy</li>
          <li>Postgraduate qualification(s) - certified true copy</li>
          <li>A referral letter from course supervisor (for Candidate Members only)</li>
          <li>Online transfer/Cheque/banker’s order addressed to the Academy of Medicine of Malaysia</li>
        </ol>


        <b>Account Name : Academy of Medicine of Malaysia</b> <br>
        <b>Account No : 8731 0377 3485</b> <br>
        <b>Bank : Standard Chartered Bank</b> <br><br>

        <p>Email to: secretariat@acadmed.my</p>
        <br>

